✅ What is _app.js and what is its use in Next.js?
_app.js is a custom App component in Next.js that acts as a wrapper for all pages in an application.
It allows you to initialize pages, maintain global state, apply global layouts, and include global styles.
📍 It is part of the Pages Router (pages/_app.js).

🔹 Core Purpose of _app.js
1️⃣ Wraps All Pages
Every page in the pages directory is rendered through _app.js.

function MyApp({ Component, pageProps }) {
  return <Component {...pageProps} />;
}
export default MyApp;
	• Component → the active page
	• pageProps → props returned from data‑fetching methods
✅ Runs on every page navigation

2️⃣ Apply Global Styles
Global CSS can only be imported inside _app.js.
import '../styles/globals.css';
✅ Ensures consistent styling across the app

3️⃣ Maintain Global State / Providers
Use _app.js to wrap pages with providers:
	• Redux
	• Context API
	• Theme providers
	• Authentication providers

<AppProvider>
  <Component {...pageProps} />
</AppProvider>
✅ State persists across route changes

4️⃣ Define Global Layouts
You can apply a common layout (header, footer, sidebar):

<Layout>
  <Component {...pageProps} />
</Layout>
``
✅ Avoids repeating layout code on every page

5️⃣ Handle Page-Level Custom Layouts
Supports per‑page layouts:

Component.getLayout =
  Component.getLayout || ((page) => page);
return Component.getLayout(<Component {...pageProps} />);
✅ Useful for dashboards, auth pages, etc.

🔹 What _app.js is NOT Used For
❌ It does not define routes
❌ It does not replace _document.js
❌ It does not render HTML <body> or <html>

🔄 _app.js vs _document.js
File	Purpose
_app.js	Wraps pages, global state, layouts
_document.js	Customize HTML, <head>, <body>

🧠 Interview‑Ready Answer (30 Seconds)
	_app.js is a custom App component in Next.js that wraps all pages.
	It is used to apply global styles, manage global state, add layouts, and initialize shared logic across pages.
	It runs for every page and ensures consistency across the application.

⚠️ Important (Modern Next.js)
	• _app.js is used with the Pages Router
	• In the App Router, similar functionality is handled by: 
		○ layout.js
		○ providers
		○ Server Components

✅ Real‑World Example
In an enterprise app (like Cognizant projects):
